description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;&quot;A very welcoming place to work as a locum, flexible shift pattern. I felt part of the team straightaway. Nice varied workload supported by experienced nursing staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hereford is a charming city with beautiful surroundings, especially good for cyclists.&quot; MB Bank SpDr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for Consultants, Specialty Doctors and SHO’s to join our Bank team within our Emergency Medical department at Wye Valley NHS Trust located in Herefordshire. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Acute services for the trust are based at the County Hospital; it provides acute care not only for Herefordshire but also for many patients coming from Powys and Gwent, in total serving a population in excess of 230,000.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Bank Doctor you will provide on-site medical support to admitting Consultants, Clinicians and Nursing Staff and will ensure that patients experience the highest level of care and service at Wye Valley NHS Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To join, you must:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently be registered with the GMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be eligible to work in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pass an enhanced DBS check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimum of 6 months&#39; NHS experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a friendly, established team who can offer you valuable support and coaching from our highly skilled consultants and medical professionals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will work on an ad hoc shift basis so that cover is provided in the Emergency Department 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If the above sounds interesting and you would like the opportunity to further develop your skills and be part of our Amazing team we would love to hear from you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
